-- CVC Is Considered Among Preferred Bidders for Picard, La Tribune Reports
-- Stephen Taylor
-- 2010-07-15T05:22:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/cvc-is-considered-among-preferred-bidders-for-picard-la-tribune-reports.html

          
          
             CVC Capital Partners Ltd. is
considered as one of the preferred bidders for French frozen-
food retailer Picard Surgeles,  La Tribune  reported, citing
unidentified people close to the matter.  
 CVC, based in London, has been one of the most active
bidders for the company, the newspaper said. BC Partners,
Picardâ€™s owner, is seeking to get lenders to agree on a debt-
financing plan of about 1 billion euros, of which 700 million
euros would be in senior debt, according to La Tribune.  
